<section class="page__section examples">
	<div class="container _sm">

		<details>
			<summary><h2 style="display: inline-block">Examples</h2></summary>

			<p style="margin-top: 1rem"><b>picture</b> component uses <b>eleventy-img</b> plugin to generate multiple sizes and&nbsp;formats of images and <b>picture</b> tag for them.</p>
			<p>The list of widths: 640, 960, 1280, 1920, 2560.
			<p>And formats: avif, webp and original image format.</p>
			<p>But it never upscales images larger than original size.</p>

			<p style="margin-top: 2rem"><b>button</b> component:</p>
			{{ component('button', {
				text: 'Отправить',
				iconName: 'arrow-right',
				iconAttr: 'width="25" height="25"'
			}) }}

			<p style="margin-top: 2rem"><b>icon</b> component (SVG-sprite):</p>
			{{ component('icon', {
				iconName: 'arrow-right',
				attr: 'width="50" height="50"'
			}) }}

			<p style="margin-top: 2rem">Example of using <b>for</b> tag and <b>range()</b> function:</p>
			{% for i in range(1, 13)  %}
				<span>{{ i }}</span>
			{% endfor %}

			{% if project.env === 'development' %}
				<div style="margin-top: 2rem">
					<p><b>*Debug*</b></p>
					<p>*Эта информация будет выводиться только при <b>project.env&nbsp;==&nbsp;'development'</b>*</p>
				</div>
			{% endif %}

			<p style="margin-top: 2rem">More information on:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="https://mozilla.github.io/nunjucks/templating.html" target="_blank">Nunjucks docs</a></li>
				<li><a href="https://www.11ty.dev/docs/languages/nunjucks/" target="_blank">Eleventy docs</a></li>
			</ul>
		</details>
	</div>
</section>
